    "objective": "“to establish a PPK model for VPA in Chinese adult epileptic patients and to demonstrate its use in dose individualization.”",
    "covariates": "Tested: SEX, AGE, WT, DDVPA, formulation, comedication (CBZ, PHT, PHB, TPM) Included: WT, DOSE, CBZ, PHT, PHB",
    "observations": "A nonlinear relationship between DDVPA and CLVPA, as reported in other studies, may be result of VPA protein binding increasing CL as the daily dose of VPA increases. A nonlinear relationship between WT and VPA CL, agreement with other studies. May be due to body size and the development/functionality of organs in elimination. Comedication increases VPA CL in model The goodness-of-fit plots obtained from the basic and final model show significant improvement in the final model with the inclusion of covariates for observed (DV) versus population prediction (PRED). Limitations possible due to model generalization.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "1 compartment model, first-order absorption and elimination",
    "equations": "CL=theta1*((WT/60)**theta2)*(DOSE**theta3)*(theta4**CBZ)*(theta5**PHT)*(theta6**PHB)*exp(eta1) V = theta7*WT KA = theta8 Cobs=Cipred+eps1 DOSE: VPA dose in mg/day CBZ: comedication with carbamazepine (1: yes, 0: no) PHT: comedication with phenytoin (1: yes, 0: no) PHB: comedication with phenobarbital (1: yes, 0: no)",
